The fix is to use more powerful tactics that can bridge the gap between `y` (an `F p` variable) and `y.val` (its `ZMod.val` component).

```tactics
import Mathlib

open ZMod

theorem ZMod.val_add_one_lt_pow (p : ℕ) (hp : Nat.Prime p) (hp2 : p > 2) (n : ℕ) (hn : 2 ^ (n + 1) < p) (y : F p) (hy : ZMod.val y < 2 ^ n) : ZMod.val (y + 1) < 2 ^ n := by
  have h1 : ZMod.val (y + 1) = ZMod.val y + 1 := by
    simp [ZMod.val_add]
  rw [h1]
  omega
```

